title: Trabantem do posledního dechu
overview: Probably the most famous Czech traveler of today, Dan Přibáň, has undertaken his most challenging expedition yet. The crews of two yellow Trabants, a Polish Fiat (aka Maluch), a Čezeta, a Jawa, and even two wheelchairs set off from Perth, Australia, and during their six-month adventure traveled through East Timor, Indonesia, Malaysia, and Thailand.
